  • Are you passionate about .NET technology?
  • Are you a team builder, a team player, a leader extraordinaire?
  • Do you find yourself constantly looking for ways to do better, be better and build better software?
  • If yes to all, we would like to talk to you!
Responsibilities:
  • Design, develop and deliver code that is necessary to support new feature developments and enhancements in an agile environment
  • Work closely with our derivative and risk teams to integrate best practices in the development of analytical tools and processes.
  • Work extensively with large data sets and have the ability to optimize and create efficient data models and SQL queries for performance.
  • Interface with 3rd party data vendors to consume 3rd Party APIs
  • Effectively communicate and document the application architecture, utilizing industry standards as part of a team.
  • Deliver unit tests with all code to prove correctness, robustness, and scalability
Qualifications:
  • A minimum of 5 years software development experience
  • Experience with REST API, Web APIs, RESTFUL Web Services
  • Experience with C#, MS SQL, JavaScript
  • Strong experience in one or more of the following technologies: ASP.NET MVC, Web API
  • Experience with modern UI web development i.e. , Angular, Typescript
  • Strong experience with SQL Server and database design
  • Knowledge of GPU/CUDA programming and programming for and deploying applications on the cloud is preferred.
  • Knowledge of SOLID principles is preferred
Salary: $115.000 - $125,000
